reviewText: My youngest daughter loves Doc McStuffins and she watches this almost every day. This is a great collection of the first season's episodes that will keep my daughter asking for more for the foreseeable future. What I love about the series is the fact that each episode has great messages about friendship, caring, and so much more which are all things that I want my daughters to learn about. The DVD was so entertaining and I have to say that any person who is already a fan will want this for their DVD collection, and if you have not seen it yet, I highly encourage the show for any pre-school age child, as (at least in my case) my daughter and I would give it two thumbs up!

reviewText: Doc McStuffins: Friendship Is The Best Medicine is a 2012 Disney DVD compilation of five episodes of the ground-breaking Disney Junior original series. This DVD features Doc Dottie McStuffins, a six-year-old girl who has a special and magical talent for talking to toys that comes to life and has  the gift of healing them when they are sick, and by "sick" they are either broken of damaged. Doc also can gives good advice on good health after every episode. There are no special features and only one Disney sneak peek, but that did not tarnish the fun and educational values Doc McStuffins can provide for the young viewers. Doc McStuffins is the best new Disney character and one that will earn the respect of every medical professional worldwide. :)
summary: Doc's Has The Prescription For Fun And Learning.

reviewText: This is a DVD about a preschool girl playing doctor to her and her friends' toys.  She is always successful.  What I like most about this is the compassion shown toward life, even though toys are used.  This show is on Disney Jr, and is fairly new.  I even enjoy watching it.  It is A 1 Disney quality.  Little Doc McStuffins' mother is very supportive, which I like as a parent quality.  I would buy future episodes.
